{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"tree":1},[2,26,45,59],{"slug":3,"title":4,"pages":5},"start","Start",[6,14,20],{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":8,"path":9,"title":10,"description":11,"order":12,"verified":13},"claw","install","/content/claw/docs/start/install.md","Install","Get the NullClaw binary via Homebrew, Docker, or a source build with Zig 0.16.0.",1,"v2026.5.29",{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":15,"path":16,"title":17,"description":18,"order":19,"verified":13},"quickstart","/content/claw/docs/start/quickstart.md","Quickstart","From a fresh install to a first conversation and a running gateway.",2,{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":21,"path":22,"title":23,"description":24,"order":25,"verified":13},"first-channel","/content/claw/docs/start/first-channel.md","Your first channel","Connect NullClaw to Telegram (or any of the 26 channels) and lock it down with allowlists.",3,{"slug":27,"title":28,"pages":29},"configure","Configure",[30,35,40],{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":31,"path":32,"title":33,"description":34,"order":12,"verified":13},"configuration","/content/claw/docs/configure/configuration.md","Configuration","One JSON file at ~/.nullclaw/config.json — OpenClaw-compatible, snake_case, no magic.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":36,"path":37,"title":38,"description":39,"order":19,"verified":13},"providers","/content/claw/docs/configure/providers.md","Providers","Connect ~60 model providers, set the default route, and add fallbacks and auto-routing.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":41,"path":42,"title":43,"description":44,"order":25,"verified":13},"memory","/content/claw/docs/configure/memory.md","Memory","Hybrid search over SQLite by default, nine other engines when you need them, and CLI tools to keep it clean.",{"slug":46,"title":47,"pages":48},"operate","Operate",[49,54],{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":50,"path":51,"title":52,"description":53,"order":12,"verified":13},"gateway-and-service","/content/claw/docs/operate/gateway-and-service.md","Gateway and service","Run NullClaw long-term — the HTTP gateway, pairing, cron endpoints, and background service mode.",{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":55,"path":56,"title":57,"description":58,"order":19,"verified":13},"security","/content/claw/docs/operate/security.md","Security","The layers NullClaw enforces by default, the settings that widen them, and how to audit for leaked secrets.",{"slug":60,"title":61,"pages":62},"reference","Reference",[63],{"siteId":7,"section":60,"slug":64,"path":65,"title":66,"description":67,"order":12,"verified":13},"cli","/content/claw/docs/reference/cli.md","CLI reference","Every nullclaw command, grouped by task — setup, runtime, channels, cron, memory, automation flags, and build flags."],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"doc":1,"raw":10,"dateModified":34,"sectionTitle":35,"prev":36,"next":42},{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":4,"path":5,"title":6,"description":7,"order":8,"verified":9,"body":10,"html":11,"toc":12},"claw","start","quickstart","/content/claw/docs/start/quickstart.md","Quickstart","From a fresh install to a first conversation and a running gateway.",2,"v2026.5.29","\nYou have the binary. This page takes you from zero config to a working agent and a long-running runtime in about five minutes.\n\n## 1. Onboard\n\nThe fastest path is one command with a provider key:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw onboard --api-key sk-... --provider openrouter\n```\n\nPrefer to be walked through it? The interactive wizard covers providers, channels, memory and more:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw onboard --interactive\n```\n\nYou can also set provider, model and memory backend in one go:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw onboard --api-key ... --provider ... --model ... --memory ...\n```\n\nEither way, onboarding writes a single JSON config to `~/.nullclaw/config.json`. That file is the whole recipe — see [Configuration](/docs/configure/configuration/) for what's in it.\n\n## 2. Say hello\n\nSend a single message:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw agent -m \"Hello, nullclaw!\"\n```\n\nOr start an interactive chat:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw agent\n```\n\nInside the interactive session, `/model` shows the current model and routing status, and `/config reload` hot-reloads supported keys from `config.json` without a restart.\n\n## 3. Start the runtime\n\n`gateway` is the long-running mode: it starts the HTTP gateway, all configured channels, the heartbeat, and the cron scheduler in one process.\n\n```bash\nnullclaw gateway                # default: 127.0.0.1:3000\nnullclaw gateway --port 8080    # custom port\n```\n\nConfirm it is up:\n\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:3000/health\n```\n\nThe gateway binds to loopback by default and refuses a public bind without a tunnel or an explicit override — see [Security](/docs/operate/security/) before exposing anything.\n\n## 4. Check the runtime\n\nTwo commands cover most \"is it working?\" questions:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw status   # full system status\nnullclaw doctor   # diagnostics with exact error details\n```\n\nIf something misbehaves, `nullclaw agent --verbose` shows what a foreground run is doing.\n\n## Coming from OpenClaw?\n\nNullClaw uses the same config structure as OpenClaw, and there is a one-command migration for config and memory:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw migrate openclaw --dry-run   # preview first\nnullclaw migrate openclaw             # then do it\n```\n\n## Where things live\n\n| Path | What it is |\n| --- | --- |\n| `~/.nullclaw/config.json` | The single config file, created by `onboard` |\n| `~/.nullclaw/workspace` | The agent's working directory (file access is scoped here by default) |\n| `~/.nullclaw/logs/` | Daemon logs when running as a service |\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Pre-1.0: config and CLI may change between releases.\n\n## Next\n\nWire up Telegram or another messenger in [Your first channel](/docs/start/first-channel/), or jump straight to [Providers](/docs/configure/providers/) to tune models and routing.\n","\u003Cp>You have the binary. This page takes you from zero config to a working agent and a long-running runtime in about five minutes.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"1-onboard\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-1-onboard\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-1-onboard\">1. Onboard\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#1-onboard\" aria-label=\"Permalink to 1. Onboard\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>The fastest path is one command with a provider key:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> onboard\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --api-key\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> sk-...\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --provider\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> openrouter\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Prefer to be walked through it? The interactive wizard covers providers, channels, memory and more:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> onboard\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --interactive\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>You can also set provider, model and memory backend in one go:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> onboard\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --api-key\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> ...\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --provider\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> ...\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> ...\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --memory\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> ...\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Either way, onboarding writes a single JSON config to \u003Ccode>~/.nullclaw/config.json\u003C/code>. That file is the whole recipe — see \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/configuration/\">Configuration\u003C/a> for what&#39;s in it.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"2-say-hello\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-2-say-hello\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-2-say-hello\">2. Say hello\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#2-say-hello\" aria-label=\"Permalink to 2. Say hello\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Send a single message:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> agent\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> -m\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"Hello, nullclaw!\"\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Or start an interactive chat:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> agent\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Inside the interactive session, \u003Ccode>/model\u003C/code> shows the current model and routing status, and \u003Ccode>/config reload\u003C/code> hot-reloads supported keys from \u003Ccode>config.json\u003C/code> without a restart.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"3-start-the-runtime\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-3-start-the-runtime\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-3-start-the-runtime\">3. Start the runtime\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#3-start-the-runtime\" aria-label=\"Permalink to 3. Start the runtime\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>\u003Ccode>gateway\u003C/code> is the long-running mode: it starts the HTTP gateway, all configured channels, the heartbeat, and the cron scheduler in one process.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> gateway\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">                # default: 127.0.0.1:3000\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> gateway\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --port\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> 8080\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">    # custom port\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Confirm it is up:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">curl\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> http://127.0.0.1:3000/health\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>The gateway binds to loopback by default and refuses a public bind without a tunnel or an explicit override — see \u003Ca href=\"/docs/operate/security/\">Security\u003C/a> before exposing anything.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"4-check-the-runtime\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-4-check-the-runtime\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-4-check-the-runtime\">4. Check the runtime\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#4-check-the-runtime\" aria-label=\"Permalink to 4. Check the runtime\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Two commands cover most &quot;is it working?&quot; questions:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> status\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">   # full system status\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> doctor\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">   # diagnostics with exact error details\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>If something misbehaves, \u003Ccode>nullclaw agent --verbose\u003C/code> shows what a foreground run is doing.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"coming-from-openclaw\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-coming-from-openclaw\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-coming-from-openclaw\">Coming from OpenClaw?\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#coming-from-openclaw\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Coming from OpenClaw?\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>NullClaw uses the same config structure as OpenClaw, and there is a one-command migration for config and memory:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> migrate\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> openclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --dry-run\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">   # preview first\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> migrate\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> openclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">             # then do it\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"where-things-live\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-where-things-live\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-where-things-live\">Where things live\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#where-things-live\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Where things live\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"table-scroll\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Data table: Path, What it is\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ctable>\n\u003Cthead>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Cth>Path\u003C/th>\n\u003Cth>What it is\u003C/th>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/thead>\n\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>~/.nullclaw/config.json\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>The single config file, created by \u003Ccode>onboard\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>~/.nullclaw/workspace\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>The agent&#39;s working directory (file access is scoped here by default)\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>~/.nullclaw/logs/\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Daemon logs when running as a service\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/tbody>\n\u003C/table>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Caside class=\"callout callout--note\">\u003Cdiv class=\"callout-title\">Note\u003C/div>\u003Cp>Pre-1.0: config and CLI may change between releases.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/aside>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"next\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-next\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-next\">Next\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#next\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Next\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Wire up Telegram or another messenger in \u003Ca href=\"/docs/start/first-channel/\">Your first channel\u003C/a>, or jump straight to \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/providers/\">Providers\u003C/a> to tune models and routing.\u003C/p>\n",[13,16,19,22,25,28,31],{"id":14,"text":15,"depth":8},"1-onboard","1. Onboard",{"id":17,"text":18,"depth":8},"2-say-hello","2. Say hello",{"id":20,"text":21,"depth":8},"3-start-the-runtime","3. Start the runtime",{"id":23,"text":24,"depth":8},"4-check-the-runtime","4. Check the runtime",{"id":26,"text":27,"depth":8},"coming-from-openclaw","Coming from OpenClaw?",{"id":29,"text":30,"depth":8},"where-things-live","Where things live",{"id":32,"text":33,"depth":8},"next","Next","2026-07-18","Start",{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":37,"path":38,"title":39,"description":40,"order":41,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":35},"install","/content/claw/docs/start/install.md","Install","Get the NullClaw binary via Homebrew, Docker, or a source build with Zig 0.16.0.",1,{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":43,"path":44,"title":45,"description":46,"order":47,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":35},"first-channel","/content/claw/docs/start/first-channel.md","Your first channel","Connect NullClaw to Telegram (or any of the 26 channels) and lock it down with allowlists.",3],"uses":{"params":["section","slug"]}}]}
